article.headline: Cordilia scores 21, Mount St. Mary's downs Fairfield 101-94
article.description: — Jedy Cordilia's 21 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Fairfield 101-94 on Sunday.
article.linkText: Cordilia scores 21, Mount St. Mary's downs Fairfield 101-94
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- — Jedy Cordilia's 21 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Fairfield 101-94 on Sunday. Cordilia also had seven rebounds for the Mountaineers (6-3, 1-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Dola Adebayo scored 15 points while shooting 5 of 7 from the field and 4 for 4 from the free-throw line and added nine rebounds, five assists, and four blocks. Dallas Hobbs shot 4 of 9 from the field, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the foul line to finish with 14 points. Prophet Johnson led the Stags (5-5, 1-1) in scoring, finishing with 22 points, 10 rebounds, five assists and two steals. Braden Sparks added 16 points and four assists for Fairfield. Jamie Bergens had 15 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
